                "name": "Bountiful Fruits",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "Once per week, a flowering lattice produces a handful of small fruits or berries that remain ripe for 1 week. Eating all of the fruit takes 1 minute and affects the eater as if she had consumed a berry affected by <i>goodberry</i>."
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Pollen",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "Once every 1d4 rounds, a flowering lattice can expel a cloud of pollen in a 10-foot cone. Creatures in the area are dazzled for 2 rounds (Fortitude DC 11 negates). If a creature currently dazzled by the pollen is affected again, it is blinded for 1 round (Fortitude DC 11 negates). The save DC is Constitution-based and includes a +2 racial bonus."
